commitResults.messageTitle: Add new field under a person, income
commitResults.messageBody:
There is no current field to represent the income of a saved contact.
This information is important to know when serving customers.

Creating this field allows for contacts to have an associated income
level.

As of v1.2, the `add` and `edit` commands can be used to add a new
contact with the income field being mandatory, and edit an existing
contact's income level accordingly.

Tests broke because of the new definition of person and its constructor.
In addition, changes to equality logic broke some existing tests.

Adding income as a parameter fixes the tests.
Adjusting the equality logic tests, such that a person is equal to
another person if their
- name
- email
- address
are equal.

We will need to discuss criteria for two persons being equal to each
other and adjusting our test logic accordingly.

commitResults.messageTitle: Update dg and ug to match mvp feature spec
Add remark field to 'add' and 'edit' + minor fixes
commitResults.messageBody:
The remark command is the only way to add and edit remarks to a person.
Using this separate command from `add` and `edit` is not only unintuitive
but also slows down users.

Adding the functionality of the `remark` command to `add` and `edit`
will allow us to improve on these 2 aspects.

As of v1.3, the `add` and `edit` commands can be used to add a new
remark, using the `rn/` flag. And for `edit` the `ra/` flag can be used
to append a new remark onto existing remarks. These flags remain
optional.

Aside from this the following minor changes are made:
- Add error message for concurrent `rn/` and `ra/` messages being
  specified in `Messages` class.
- Update format for the status bar message that is shown to users when a
  person is added or edited to include remark in `Messages` class.
- Add remark constraints message in `Remark` class.
- Add validity test for remark in `Remark` class.
- Add method to combine multiple remark in `Remark` class.

commitResults.messageBody:
The current tests do not test `rn/` and `ra/` in both add and edit
command tests.

The following tests are added:
- AddCommandIntegrationTest:
	- Test for whether indicating tier and remark leads to successful adding
- EditCommandTest:
	- Test whether specifying append remark in edit command leads
	  to a successful appending onto the existing remark.
	- Test whether specifying a new remark in edit command
	  overwrites any existing remark.
- EditCommandParserTest:
	- Test whether specifying both `rn/` and `ra/` flags in edit
	  command leads to an exception and error message shown.

The following minor changes are made as well:
- Adding a `APPEND_REMARK_DESC_BOB` in CommandTestUtil.
- Adding a `withAppendedRemark` method in EditPersonDescriptorBuilder.
- Removing a default value for `appendedRemark` field in EditCommand
  file.

commitResults.messageTitle: Merge branch 'status-dev' of https://github.com/ZShunRen/tp into status-dev
Add status attribute + other minor fixes
commitResults.messageBody:
There is no way to indicate if follow-up action is needed for a
particular customer, which is usually the case with financial services.

Adding the status attribute helps the user differentiate between clients
who may need follow-up action, and works in tandem with remark, where
case details can be inserted.

Other small changes include:
- Refactoring `Person::isSamePerson` method to use name, phone and email as
  checks for equality.
- Refactoring `Person::equals` method to use `Person::isSamePerson`
  method when checking for equality, which makes the code more
  maintainable as equality logic is only specified once.
Implement confirmation check
